title: Incoming passengers to lose duty-free concessions on tobacco products
content_text:
p> �@�@�@The Financial Secretary, Mr John C Tsang, in his Budget speech today (February 24) proposed to abolish duty-free concessions on tobacco products for incoming passengers to Hong Kong as a means to further protect public health. �@�@�@Elaborating on the proposed arrangements, a government spokesman said small amounts of tobacco products for own consumption would be exempted to facilitate law enforcement.
